properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued February 29 at 4:50AM AKST until February 29 at 12:00PM AKST by NWS Fairbanks, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills to 45 below occurring. The cold
wind chills will cause frostbite in as little as 10 minutes to
exposed skin.

* WHERE...Baldwin Peninsula and Selawik Valley.

* WHEN...Now to noon.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Conditions will become less extreme this
afternoon as winds decrease.
properties.instruction:
A Wind Chill Advisory means that cold air and sustained wind
speeds of 15 mph or more will create low wind chills. Frost bite
and hypothermia can occur if precautions are not taken.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL NOON AKST TODAY
